Though given to outlaws, it shall never be
broken
but for cause, replied Johnson. But the
rebels
,
drunken with their first success, will soon
supply
us with legitimate grounds for disregarding the
pledge they have wrung from us.
Well, you white men know best how far ye may
trust each other, observed the chief, with a
significant
and pitying smile, while, in drawing his mantle
around him to depart, he muttered less audibly
beneath
